    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Drawing upon the order and stability of the lawful outer planes, you stabilize a creature&rsquo;s form with a touch. The target gains a +2 circumstance bonus against transmutation spells and effects. Physical stability counters @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.kzOemsOWuqgbbGZw]{Baleful Polymorph} and @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.gNgdSyi4pXQmasmc]{Polymorph}, and it counters and negates @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.xledsFeEKm5em0Dt]{Fluidity Of Form}. If you cast physical stability on a creature already under the effects of a transmutation effect, you can try to dispel one transmutation effect affecting the target. If you do, attempt a dispel check (1d20 + caster level) with a DC equal to 11 + the caster level of the transmutation effect to end the effect.</p>"
